{
  "texts": [
    "There have been attempts to improve the coverage of various stereotypes and demographic groups in the bias evaluation literature (Guo and Caliskan, 2021).",
    "And, also to leverage from the fields of psychology and social science to evaluate bias across more social dimensions (Caliskan et al., 2017; Du et al., 2019), but these are based on pre-trained word embeddings.",
    "Although these have alleviated some of the issues, they do not allow us to measure these harms in a continuous and comprehensive way, specifically for new LLM technology.",
    "In particular, we have concerns in the following three areas that might inhibit such a measurement of LLM technology:",
    "• Limited Demographic Categories: Most existing methodologies focus on a narrow set of demographic categories like gender or race (Talat et al., 2022)."
  ]
}